From: Emir <celikemirhan6@gmail.com>
Date: Sat, 2 May 2026 21:19:33 +0300
Subject: [PATCH] emir_flatpack: lossless tightening of qpose14 (-5,625 bytes)
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Same renderer/weights/masks/pose as qpose14 (PR #63) — only the packing
changes:

- Strip pickle/torch.save overhead from model.pt by writing tensors as
  flat binary in a fixed schema baked into inflate.py.
- Concatenate mask + flat model + pose into one buffer with a 12-byte
  length header + 1-byte order tag, then brotli q=11 over the whole
  thing. Encoder tries all 6 stream orderings; pose|mask|model wins.

Result: 281,948-byte archive vs qpose14's 287,573, distortion identical,
expected leaderboard score ~0.32 (qpose14 0.323 - 0.0038).

Credits qpose14 (PR #63), quantizr (PR #55), unified_brotli (PR #64).
